cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.MA 

This paper deals with information theoretical approaches to statistics, specifically the minimization of Csiszár f-divergences. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) in its examination of the Pythagorean property.
